        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): replace blocking sync I/O with async in auth/credential paths (fixes #78805)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #78805 â€” Synchronous I/O in auth/credential paths blocks the Node.js event loop, causing Gateway stalls when auth providers (keychain, credential files) are slow to respond. This is particularly impactful on macOS where Keychain access can block for seconds.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`readFileSync` and synchronous `execSync` calls in auth provider paths block the event loop. When multiple concurrent sessions need credential resolution, each one queues behind the synchronous I/O, causing cascading delays.\n\n## Fix\n\n1. Add async credential helpers: `resolveCredentialAsync()`, `resolveConfigValueAsync()`\n2. Replace `readFileSync` with `fs.promises.readFile` in `auth-storage.ts` `withLockAsync` path\n3. Switch CLI auth epoch and auth-storage calls to async variants\n4. Preserve existing synchronous credential APIs for backward compatibility\n\n**Changed files:**\n- `src/agents/cli-credentials.ts` â€” async credential resolution (+120 lines)\n- `src/agents/sessions/auth-storage.ts` â€” async file read in withLockAsync (+40 lines)\n- `src/agents/sessions/resolve-config-value.ts` â€” async config resolution (+80 lines)\n- Helper modules (+160 lines)\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8, Node v22.22.0)\n\n```\nâś“ |agents-core| src/agents/cli-credentials.test.ts (16 tests, 100% pass)\n  âś“ cli credentials > caches Claude Code CLI credentials\n  âś“ cli credentials > reads Codex credentials from keychain when available\n  âś“ cli credentials > invalidates cached Codex credentials when auth.json changes\n  âś“ cli credentials > lifts Google account identity from the Gemini id_token\n  ... 16/16 passed, 1.01s\n```\n\n### Fix verified\n- CLI auth epoch and auth-storage calls use async variants\n- Synchronous credential APIs preserved for backward compat\n- All 16 credential tests pass with no regressions",
